<TITLE> Families complain of slow rescue work </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Barisal, Feb 19 (bdnews24.com)  The families of those missing after a passenger launch sank in the Kirtankhola river near Barisal town early Thursday have complained of a slow rescue operation. At least one person drowned and fifty were missing in the accident that occurred at Beltala around 6:30am as a sand-laden cargo vessel hit the ML Happy that was carrying over 100 passengers. Barisal deputy commissioner Mushfiq Ahmed Shamim, quoting BIWTA authorities and Kotwali police, told bdnews24.com that a woman's body had been recovered so far. The dead woman was identified as Dipti Dey, 30. Shamim said some 50 people were still missing at around 3pm. Rescue workers were struggling to lift the sunken launch some nine hours after the accident. Rescue vessels reached the spot some two hours after the accident, said Shamim. The ML Happy had been heading towards Patarhat from Barisal. The accident occured some 3km out from the district town. bdnews24.c
